{
  "texts": [
    "To evaluate the quality of the synthetic image based on voxels, the most used similarity metrics are Mean Absolute Error (MAE), Structural Similarity (SSIM), and Peak Signal to Noise Ratio (PSNR).",
    "Besides voxel-based metrics, geometric accuracy can also be assessed by comparing delineated structures with corresponding voxel-based metrics.",
    "In terms of evaluating the accuracy of depicting specific tissue classes and structures, the Dice Similarity Coefficient (DSC) is a commonly used metric.",
    "DSC is calculated after applying morphological operations to binary masks and applying a threshold to Computed Tomography (CT) and synthetic CT (sCT).",
    "In addition to the Hausdorff distance, the mean absolute surface distance can be used to assess the segmentation accuracy, as it measures the distance between two contour sets (74)."
  ]
}